Civil servants in Bauchi state have been advised to be proactive and vigilant in the discharge of their official duties in order to move the service forward positively. The advice was given by the newly appointed Acting Head of Civil Service in the state, Alh Ahmad Abubakar Ma’aji when he officially assumed duty on Wednesday. While speaking after taking over the mantle of leadership from his immediate predecessor, Nasiru Yalwa, Alh Ahmad Abubakar appreciated God Almighty for making it possible for Governor Bala Muhammad to appoint him to that position and pledged to justify the confidence reposed in him. ALSO READ: Bayelsa poll: Douye shuns Code of Conduct Bureau over alleged non assets declaration OCP joins World Business Council for sustainable development Buhari, Putin to strengthen Nigeria-Russia relations Nigeria ranks highest among countries with burden of sickle… UPDATE: FEC okays April 18 as take-off date for new minimum… Ahmad Abubakar promised to operate an open-door policy throughout his tenure and enjoined civil servants to strictly adhere to Civil Service rules and regulations for optimal performance. Speaking earlier, the former Head of Civil Service, Alh Nasiru Mohammad Yalwa commended the Permanent Secretaries for their support throughout his three months period and urged them to extend same to his successor for the development of the state. In his remarks, Special Adviser to Governor Bala Muhammad on Civil Service Affairs, Mr Abdon Dalla Gin charged Civil Servants to always be punctual at all times to earn their salaries. He commended Governor Bala Mohammad for the following seniority in the appointment of the new Acting Head of Civil Service in the state. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
